# Yosys Synthesis Flow for Low-Power ALU

## File: synth.ys

```tcl
# ----------------------------------
# Read RTL
# ----------------------------------

read_verilog rtl/lp_adder.v
read_verilog rtl/low_power_alu.v

# ----------------------------------
# Set Top Module
# ----------------------------------

hierarchy -check -top low_power_alu

# ----------------------------------
# Generic RTL Optimizations
# ----------------------------------

proc
opt
fsm
opt

# ----------------------------------
# Technology Independent Mapping
# ----------------------------------

techmap
opt

# ----------------------------------
# Resource Sharing
# ----------------------------------

share

# ----------------------------------
# Arithmetic Optimizations
# ----------------------------------

alumacc

# ----------------------------------
# Logic Optimization
# ----------------------------------

opt_clean
opt

# ----------------------------------
# Statistics
# ----------------------------------

stat

# ----------------------------------
# Generate Netlist
# ----------------------------------

write_json reports/alu.json

write_verilog \
reports/alu_synth.v

# ----------------------------------
# Resource Report
# ----------------------------------

tee -o reports/yosys_stat.txt stat
```

---

# Run Yosys

Linux:

```bash
yosys synth.ys
```

Windows:

```cmd
yosys synth.ys
```

Expected Output:

```text
=== low_power_alu ===

Number of wires:
Number of cells:
Number of public wires:
...
```

---

